<TEXT>
one policeman was killed and eight people were 
wounded as leftist guerrillas carried out a dozen attacks in lima 
half of them against offices of the governing centerleft aprista 
party authorities said tuesday 
elsewhere police in the jungle town of mazamari 195 miles east 
of lima shot and killed two men on a motorcycle late sunday after 
they ignored an order to stop 
police said the men were suspected of belonging to the 
maoinspired shining path guerrilla group and were carrying dynamite 
police said shining path guerrillas bombed the six political 
offices shortly before midnight monday as their answer to president 
alan garcias vow to step up the battle against insurgency 
five aprista members were wounded by flying glass and blast 
fragments police said 
in a simultaneous attack rebels from the procuban tupac amaru 
revolutionary movement fired on a patrol car from a passing car 
killing one officer and wounding his partner and two passersby 
police said 
the two rebel bands are not known to be linked and police called 
the simultaneous attacks a coincidence 
shining path guerrillas also tossed bombs at a bank a police 
post a suburban municipal building and the home of an aprista 
member causing minor damage but no casualties police said 
maoist saboteurs also toppled a power pylon with explosives 
briefly blacking out a few zones in the city police said 
more than 12000 people have died in the shining paths nineyear 
insurgency to impose marxist rule 
the smaller tupac amaru group began attacks five years ago 
</TEXT>
