<TEXT>
the university of massachusetts has 
rescinded an order banning five conservative clubs at the school 
from renting meeting rooms and vending tables at the campus center 
a spokeswoman said monday 
however the campus republican club and an affiliate of a 
cambridgebased marxist group the spartacist league remain under 
the ban because of a brawl between members of those groups at the 
school feb 9 said spokeswoman jeanne hopkins 
a student was injured in the fight which was the second 
confrontation between the groups in a month the head of the school 
buildings departemnt is investigating the incident 
hopkins said the ban had been widened to other conservative 
student groups because they were suspected of renting rooms for the 
republican club in defiance of the ban 
the school lifted the ban against the other groups on friday 
hopkins said the office of student affairs felt the ban wasnt the 
most appropriate way to handle the situation 
an attorney for the republican club said he believed the ban was 
a violation of the clubs right of free speech and assembly and that 
he was speaking with university attorneys about lifting it 
i believe if we went into court it would say that the 
university deprived the group of its rights said attorney les 
black 
