resegregation of the citys schools 
the nine whites on the committee voted for the plan monday night 
the four blacks voted against and one of them john obryant said 
were going to end up where we were in court 
opponents said it may resegregate schools supporters said 
resegregation is not an issue because less than 25 percent of the 
systems 55000 students are white 
us district judge w arthur garrity jr ordered bostons 
schools desegregated in 1974 resulting in many students being bused 
outside their neighborhoods to achieve racial balance the busing 
resulted in violent protests by whites 
garrity relinquished control over the nations oldest school 
system in 1985 but the busing plan has remained in effect 
the new plan divides the city into three zones each designed to 
include people of all backgrounds 
parents will be given a choice of schools within the zone in 
which they live and will get their choice unless it causes 
overcrowding or upsets a schools racial balance 
the plan calls for all schools to reflect the racial breakdown in 
its zone 
black members of the school committee threatened to file a 
federal lawsuit to block the plan 
the national association for the advancement of colored people 
