<TEXT>
except for a brief thaw late last year 
britishiranian relations have been troubled for the past 8 years 
here is a summary 
september 1980 with irans relations with the west in turmoil 
over the seizure of the us embassy hostages britain closes its 
embassy in tehran and withdraws its staff for their protection four 
diplomats stay behind to run a british interests section in the 
swedish embassy 
november 1985 british businessman roger cooper is arrested in 
iran and accused of spying but is not charged or tried 
may 1987 police arrest an iranian diplomat in manchester on 
shoplifting charges in tehran a british diplomat is abducted and 
beaten up apparently in retaliation 
june 1987 over the years britain has slowly built up a 
19member staff in its tehran embassy but after a series of 
titfortat diplomatic expulsions triggered by the manchester 
incident london recalls all its diplomats in iran and reduces the 
iranian diplomatic presence in london to a lone charge daffaires 
september 1987 iran attacks a british tanker in the persian 
gulf britain hits back by closing the london headquarters of irans 
worldwide armspurchasing operation 
june 1988 iran and britain have talks in london on compensation 
for damage done to each others embassies in political violence in 
1979 and 1980 the successful negotiations lead to broader talks on 
britishiranian relations and agreement is reached to resume full 
diplomatic ties 
december 1988 the british embassy in tehran reopens nicholas 
nicola a british tourist held in iran for more than two years is 
freed and comes home hopes rise for the release of cooper as well 
as british hostages believed held by proiranian abductors in 
lebanon 
february 1989 ayatollah ruhollah khomeini passes a death 
sentence on british novelist salman rushdie claiming his novel 
the satanic verses blasphemes islam rushdies apology is not 
accepted in tehran cooper is given a heavy but unspecified 
sentence britain and its 11 european economic community partners 
