effort to politically realise tamil aspirations 
mostly hindu tamils comprise 18 percent of sri lankas 16 million 
people militants claim they are discriminated against in education 
employment and culture by the predominantly buddhist sinhalese who 
make up 75 percent of the countrys population and control the 
administration and military 
