to themselves of sinking towers nomination they had hoped to avoid 
a showdown with the new president until a later date and democrat 
after democrat was eager to point out to reporters on tuesday that 
bushs other cabinet appointees have all been confirmed without a 
single negative vote 
one senior democratic senator speaking anonymously said 
majority leader george mitchell and armed services committee 
chairman sam nunn were worried about the appearance of 
partisanship in dealing with a newly elected president 
the senate armed services committee has devoted practically all 
of its time to the nomination with hearings on defense strategy 
spending procurement reform and other matters been pushed aside 
nunn dga who has spent years nurturing an image as a 
bipartisan leader of the senate on defense issues has found himself 
squarely in the middle of an issue that has become polarized almost 
entirely along party lines 
sen william cohen rmaine says he has not seen passions 
inflamed over an issue such as this one in several years and says 
it will hinder chances of formulating bipartisan defense and foreign 
policy 
democrats and some republicans whisper that jimmy carter was 
illadvised to withdraw ted sorensons nomination as cia director in 
1977 in the face of senate opposition and believe bush would be 
wiser to stand and fight than to cut his losses and signal tower to 
withdraw 
but there are other senators who have publicly or privately 
suggested that bush withdraw the nomination a move that would 
spare them the need to make an extremely tough decision on how to 
vote 
the effect on bushs ability to deal effectively on other issues 
isnt as easy to calculate 
sen james sasser dtenn said i think the president is 
upping the stake substantially i think if tower is defeated it is 
going to diminish his prestige here in congress 
but sasser who is chairman of the senate budget committee and 
thus most likely to become the senator leading the democrats into 
battle with bush says budget concerns are independent of tower 
i think the administration can recover from the tower problem 
if the nomination is defeated but i think the real question is 
whether the tower problem is symptomatic of the failure of the 
administration to get its program and its policies in a coherent and 
convincing way 
