averaged 403 per bushel compared with 401 in january and 279 
a year earlier 
rice averaged 655 per 100 pounds up from 647 in january 
rice was 937 a year earlier 
soybeans were 723 per bushel compared with 769 in january 
and 596 a year earlier 
upland cotton was reported at 531 cents per pound down from 
539 cents in january and 57 cents in february 1988 
eggs were 621 cents per dozen compared with 639 cents in 
january and 469 cents a year earlier 
milk was 1310 per 100 pounds compared with 1340 in january 
and 1230 a year earlier 
broilers were 352 cents per pound live weight compared with 
353 cents in january and 257 cents a year ago 
