us catholic educators and vatican proposals for closer church 
supervision over catholic colleges and universities 
of the upcoming meeting the pope has said it will deal with 
impressions both of his 1987 visit to the united states and a 1988 
series bishops visits with the pope 
several bishops say the visits had a mostly positive upbeat 
tone the pope is bullish on the u s church says archbiship john 
l may of st louis president of the national conference of bishops 
however the pope has pressed his insistence on doctrinal 
conformity saying of the us scene 
certain positions on the socalled right to dissent have had 
harmful repercussions on the moral conduct of a number of the 
