the management of a group buying the united 
states shoe corps footwear division for 4225 million says 
dramatic changes are not in store for the cincinnatibased division 
the footwear division will retain its existing management us 
shoes corporate headquarters and distribution facility in the city 
as well as the us shoe name officials said monday 
division president howard platt who will become president and 
chief executive officer of the new shoe company said the 
acquisition by a group headed by merrill lynch capital partners 
inc an affiliate of merrill lynch capital markets inc should not 
result in any job losses among its 8000 employees 
were not planning any reductions in the work force other than 
what occurs through the normal course of business platt said 
the purchase excludes us shoes cincinnatibased lenscrafters 
division which operates retail eyeglass stores and its womens 
apparel retail division based in enfield conn which operates the 
casual corner petite sophisticate and caren charles chains 
