expectations by some that the entire company would be sold 
although the domestic shoe industry has been hurt in recent years 
by foreign imports us shoes footwear business has positioned 
itself as one of the industrys strongest players through a 
combination of domestic and foreign production he said 
the division operates about 500 retail stores under the hahn and 
bannister store name and through leased departments it owns 20 
womens shoe brands including calvin klein capezio red cross 
selby liz claiborne and pappagallo 
in 1988 the footwear division which operates about 20 
manufacturing and distribution facilities in the us accounted for 
about onethird of us shoes 22 billion in sales and 57 percent 
of the the companys 52 million in profit 
the divisions domestic production represents about 10 percent to 
15 percent of the total us production of moderately priced shoes 
platt said 
